    • addHistoricalPrice

      void addHistoricalPrice​(int idUpTo, int assetID, java.lang.String unitResponsible, int price, java.time.LocalDateTime dateTime)
      Add a dummy "historical" transaction
      Parameters:
      idUpTo - ID to use for the buy order's BoughtFrom, assumed to be the sell ID
      assetID - Asset for the transaction
      unitResponsible - Unit to attach to both the buy and sell order
      price - Price to put for both orders
      dateTime - Datetime to put for both orders' dates placed and resolved

    • login

      User login​(java.lang.String username, java.lang.String password) throws common.Exceptions.IllegalString, common.Exceptions.DoesNotExist
      Validate login-- determine first whether the input username exists, then whether the input password is correct (by retrieving the user's salt string and hashed password, then hashing the input password with the salt string and checking if it matches the input password)
      Parameters:
      username - Username input string
      password - Password input string
      Returns:
      User object of the now-logged-in user if the credentials were correct
      Throws:
      common.Exceptions.IllegalString - if the input password was of an invalid format (meaning it must be incorrect)
      common.Exceptions.DoesNotExist - if the user does not exist or the password is incorrect

    • getOrdersForTable

      java.util.ArrayList<Order> getOrdersForTable​(java.lang.String unitName, boolean justMine, boolean isBuy, boolean resolvedFlag)
      Gets orders to populate an OrderTablePage
      Parameters:
      unitName - Unit name, used iff justMine
      justMine - True means "just get orders from unitName", false means "don't filter by org unit"
      isBuy - True means "get buy orders", false means "get sell orders"
      resolvedFlag - True means "get resolved orders", false means "get unresolved orders"
      Returns:
      An ArrayList of either BuyOrders or SellOrders

    • getHistoricalPrices

      java.util.TreeMap<java.time.LocalDate,​java.lang.Double> getHistoricalPrices​(int a, TradingAppData.Intervals timeInterval) throws common.Exceptions.InvalidDate, common.Exceptions.DoesNotExist
      Method that collects average prices between specified intervals for the entire data set and places them into a TreeMap. This may be used to create a price history graph.
      Parameters:
      timeInterval - the time interval in which the data will be split before calculating the averages of each interval. Constants are provided as days, 3 days, weeks, months and years.
      Returns:
      returns a TreeMap with each intervals start date as a key, with its value being the corresponding average.
      Throws:
      common.Exceptions.InvalidDate
      common.Exceptions.DoesNotExist
